well the pic linked to has no other info so its probably just a concept drawing.., also you might want to try out rainmeter, it can do virtually everything live tiles can and more <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />, although it wont be 'compatible' with any of the current live tiles, it has quite a few of its own little apps you can add.., and im sure theres a way to link to all the metro apps through it.. omnimo might be of interest to you (a rainmeter skin, that tries to mimic w8's metro UI)<br /><br />Note: im not a real fan of the windows store, and its attempt to monopolize what can and cant be installed on windows. i know there just following the standard, but there has to be a way to install modern apps outside of the store to change my vote.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Tue May 14, 2013 8:27 pm</p><hr />
